Preconditions:
The arrays `firstReward` and `secondReward` must not be null.
The arrays `firstReward` and `secondReward` must have the same length.
The value of `numberOfTypesOfCheeseForFirstMouse` must be a non-negative integer.
The value of `numberOfTypesOfCheeseForFirstMouse` must not exceed the length of the arrays `firstReward` and `secondReward`.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the maximum points the mice can achieve.
The returned value should be greater than or equal to zero.
The returned value should be the maximum points achievable when the first mouse eats exactly `numberOfTypesOfCheeseForFirstMouse` types of cheese.